vulnerabilities.explanation:
### OS Command Injection in Video Conversion Feature

**CVSS3.1 Vector**: `CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H` (Score: 8.8)

**Description:** **What:** OS Command Injection in the video conversion feature. The application takes stored user-controlled values (`video_name` and `conversion_params`) and concatenates them directly into a shell command string without sanitization or escaping.

**Why it matters:** If executed, an attacker can run arbitrary commands on the server hosting the Identity service. This can lead to complete system compromise, data exfiltration, or denial of service.

**How it can be exploited:** An authenticated user calls the video update endpoint and modifies the `video_name` or `conversion_params` fields to include shell metacharacters (e.g., `; cat /etc/passwd` or `$(whoami)`). When the server processes the request, it passes the crafted string to the operating system's command interpreter, executing the injected commands. Note: This execution path is only active if the `enable_shell_injection` configuration flag is set to `true`.

**Impact:**
Confidentiality: High | Integrity: High | Availability: High

**Affected Entry Points:**
| Type | Identifier | File | Route | Description |
|------|------------|------|-------|-------------|
| http_endpoint | `ep-updateprofilevideo` | ...ller/ProfileController.java | `PUT /identity/api/v2/user/videos/{video_id}` | Authenticated HTTP endpoint that triggers the video conversion logic. Accepts a PUT request with user-controlled fields that populate the database values used in the shell command. |

**Data Flow:**
|   Level | Name                                     | File Path                                          | Line    |
|--------:|:-----------------------------------------|:---------------------------------------------------|:--------|
|       1 | ProfileController.convertVideoEndPoint#2 | ...ava/com/crapi/controller/ProfileController.java | 144-155 |
|       2 | ProfileServiceImpl.convertVideo#2        | .../com/crapi/service/Impl/ProfileServiceImpl.java | 201-255 |
|       3 | BashCommand.executeBashCommand#1         | .../src/main/java/com/crapi/utils/BashCommand.java | 31-62   |

