public String getUserFromToken(HttpServletRequest request) throws ParseException {
  ApiType apiType = getKeyType(request);
  String token = getToken(request);
  String username = null;
  if (token != null) {
    if (apiType == ApiType.APIKEY) {
      log.debug("Token is api token");
      username = tokenProvider.getUserNameFromJwtToken(token);
    } else {
      log.debug("Token is jwt token");
      if (tokenProvider.validateJwtToken(token)) {
        username = tokenProvider.getUserNameFromJwtToken(token);
      }
    }
    // checking username from token
    if (username != null) return username;
  }
  return EStatus.INVALID.toString();
}

vulnerabilities.explanation:
### Unrestricted File Upload in Profile Picture Handler

**CVSS3.1 Vector**: `CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:H/A:H` (Score: 8.3)

**Description:** The `validateFile` method is intended to secure file uploads but performs no actual security checks. It extracts the original filename, applies a path-cleaning utility that already removes directory traversal sequences (`..`), and then runs a redundant check that will never trigger. Crucially, the method completely skips validation of the file extension, MIME type, and actual file content. It immediately returns the raw byte array of the uploaded file, effectively allowing any file type—including malicious scripts, web shells, or executable binaries—to bypass the upload pipeline unchecked. When processed downstream, these unvalidated files can be stored in predictable locations or fed into system commands, leading to Remote Code Execution (RCE) or server compromise.

**Impact:**
Attackers can upload arbitrary files (e.g., web shells, malicious scripts) to the server's upload directory. Depending on how the Identity service processes these files, this can lead to arbitrary file write, Remote Code Execution, or service disruption.

**Affected Entry Points:**
| Type | Identifier | File | Route | Description |
|------|------------|------|-------|-------------|
| http_endpoint | `ep-updateprofilepicture` | ...ller/ProfileController.java | `POST /identity/api/v2/user/pictures` | POST /identity/api/v2/user/pictures |

**Data Flow:**
|   Level | Name                                      | File Path                                          | Line   |
|--------:|:------------------------------------------|:---------------------------------------------------|:-------|
|       1 | ProfileController.updateProfilePicture#2  | ...ava/com/crapi/controller/ProfileController.java | 59-69  |
|       2 | ProfileServiceImpl.uploadProfilePicture#2 | .../com/crapi/service/Impl/ProfileServiceImpl.java | 60-82  |
|       3 | ProfileValidator.validateFile#1           | ...main/java/com/crapi/utils/ProfileValidator.java | 48-60  |

```
