**CVSS3.1 Vector**: `CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:L` (Score: 8.3)

**Description:** The `/identity/api/auth/v2/check-otp` endpoint validates one-time passwords (OTPs) without implementing rate limiting, throttling, or brute-force protection. OTPs are typically short, predictable codes (4–6 digits). Without limits on how many times an attacker can submit guesses, an automated script can rapidly iterate through possible values until one matches. This effectively bypasses the secondary authentication factor, allowing full account takeover. Additionally, the lack of request throttling allows the endpoint to be abused for denial-of-service by exhausting backend email/SMTP resources or CPU cycles.

